    <para id="id8562955">You see what happened? 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>19</m:mtext><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"19" rSup { size 8{3} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> means three 19s multiplied; 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>19</m:mtext><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow/><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"19" rSup { size 8{ cdot 4} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> means four 19s multiplied. Multiply them together, and you get <emphasis>seven</emphasis> 19s multiplied.</para>
    
