    <para id="id9316089">What does it mean to raise something to the fourth power? It means to multiply it by itself, four times. In this case, what we are multiplying by itself four times is 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>19</m:mtext><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"19" rSup { size 8{3} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, or 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mfenced open="(" close=")"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>19</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">⋅</m:mo><m:mtext>19</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">⋅</m:mo><m:mtext>19</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mfenced></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ left ("19" cdot "19" cdot "19" right )} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. Three 19s multiplied <emphasis>four times</emphasis> makes twelve 19s multiplied.</para>
    
